  "grammar_html": {
    "en": "<h3>1. Verb 'to be' – questions and negatives</h3><div style='background-color:#fff; padding:15px; border-radius:10px; border:1px dashed #bdc3c7; margin-bottom:15px;'><p style='margin:5px 0;'>For yes/no questions, put the verb 'to be' before the subject: <strong>Is she English?</strong> For negatives, add 'not': <strong>She isn't married.</strong> 'I'm not' is the negative for 'I am'.</p></div><ul style='list-style-type:none; padding-left:10px;'><li style='margin-bottom:15px;'><strong style='color:#e67e22;'>• Is</strong> she a doctor? – No, <strong style='color:#e67e22;'>she isn't</strong>.</li><li style='margin-bottom:15px;'><strong style='color:#2980b9;'>• Are</strong> you married? – No, <strong style='color:#2980b9;'>I'm not</strong>.</li><li style='margin-bottom:15px;'><strong style='color:#16a085;'>• What's</strong> her job? – <strong style='color:#16a085;'>She's</strong> a journalist.</li></ul><h3>2. Possessive 's</h3><div style='background-color:#fff; padding:15px; border-radius:10px; border:1px dashed #bdc3c7; margin-bottom:15px;'><p style='margin:5px 0;'>We use <strong>'s</strong> to show possession or relationship. It is different from <strong>'s = is</strong>.</p></div><ul style='list-style-type:none; padding-left:10px;'><li style='margin-bottom:15px;'><strong style='color:#d35400;'>• Patrick's wife</strong> = the wife of Patrick (possession)</li><li style='margin-bottom:15px;'><strong style='color:#d35400;'>• She's a teacher</strong> = She is a teacher ('s = is)</li><li style='margin-bottom:15px;'><strong style='color:#d35400;'>• His daughter's name</strong> = the name of his daughter</li></ul><h3>3. Opposites (adjectives)</h3><div style='background-color:#fff; padding:15px; border-radius:10px; border:1px dashed #bdc3c7; margin-bottom:15px;'><p style='margin:5px 0;'>Adjectives describe nouns. Here are some common opposites:</p></div><ul style='list-style-type:none; padding-left:10px;'><li style='margin-bottom:15px;'><strong style='color:#16a085;'>• big</strong> – <strong style='color:#e74c3c;'>small</strong> / <strong style='color:#16a085;'>new</strong> – <strong style='color:#e74c3c;'>old</strong></li><li style='margin-bottom:15px;'><strong style='color:#16a085;'>• cheap</strong> – <strong style='color:#e74c3c;'>expensive</strong> / <strong style='color:#16a085;'>easy</strong> – <strong style='color:#e74c3c;'>difficult</strong></li><li style='margin-bottom:15px;'><strong style='color:#16a085;'>• hot</strong> – <strong style='color:#e74c3c;'>cold</strong> / <strong style='color:#16a085;'>fast</strong> – <strong style='color:#e74c3c;'>slow</strong></li></ul>",
    "ja": "",
    "fr": "",
    "ko": ""
  },
  "vocabulary_check": {
    "en": "<div style='background:#fff5f5; border:1px solid #fed7d7; border-radius:12px; padding:20px; margin-bottom:25px;'><div style='display:flex; align-items:center; flex-wrap:wrap; gap:10px; margin-bottom:20px;'><h4 style='color:#c53030; margin:0; border-left:4px solid #f56565; padding-left:10px;'>Group 1: Verb 'to be' (negatives)</h4><span style='font-size:0.85rem; background:#f56565; color:white; padding:4px 12px; border-radius:20px;'><i class='fas fa-spell-check'></i> Word Bank: isn't, aren't, 'm not</span></div><div style='display:flex; align-items:center; flex-wrap:wrap; gap:5px; margin-bottom:15px;'>1. She <select class='vocab-select'><option value=''>── select ──</option><option value='isn't'>isn't</option><option value='aren't'>aren't</option><option value=''m not'>'m not</option></select> married.<button onclick='checkVocab(this)'>Check</button><span class='vocab-answer' data-correct='isn't' style='display:none;'></span></div><div style='display:flex; align-items:center; flex-wrap:wrap; gap:5px; margin-bottom:15px;'>2. I <select class='vocab-select'><option value=''>── select ──</option><option value='isn't'>isn't</option><option value='aren't'>aren't</option><option value=''m not'>'m not</option></select> a teacher.<button onclick='checkVocab(this)'>Check</button><span class='vocab-answer' data-correct=''m not' style='display:none;'></span></div><div style='display:flex; align-items:center; flex-wrap:wrap; gap:5px; margin-bottom:15px;'>3. You <select class='vocab-select'><option value=''>── select ──</option><option value='isn't'>isn't</option><option value='aren't'>aren't</option><option value=''m not'>'m not</option></select> from Spain.<button onclick='checkVocab(this)'>Check</button><span class='vocab-answer' data-correct='aren't' style='display:none;'></span></div></div><div style='background:#fffaf0; border:1px solid #feebc8; border-radius:12px; padding:20px; margin-bottom:25px;'><div style='display:flex; align-items:center; flex-wrap:wrap; gap:10px; margin-bottom:20px;'><h4 style='color:#c05621; margin:0; border-left:4px solid #ed8936; padding-left:10px;'>Group 2: Family words</h4><span style='font-size:0.85rem; background:#ed8936; color:white; padding:4px 12px; border-radius:20px;'><i class='fas fa-spell-check'></i> Word Bank: wife, son, daughter, brother</span></div><div style='display:flex; align-items:center; flex-wrap:wrap; gap:5px; margin-bottom:15px;'>4. Patrick's <select class='vocab-select'><option value=''>── select ──</option><option value='wife'>wife</option><option value='son'>son</option><option value='daughter'>daughter</option><option value='brother'>brother</option></select> is Brenda.<button onclick='checkVocab(this)'>Check</button><span class='vocab-answer' data-correct='wife' style='display:none;'></span></div><div style='display:flex; align-items:center; flex-wrap:wrap; gap:5px; margin-bottom:15px;'>5. Lara is Patrick's <select class='vocab-select'><option value=''>── select ──</option><option value='wife'>wife</option><option value='son'>son</option><option value='daughter'>daughter</option><option value='brother'>brother</option></select>.<button onclick='checkVocab(this)'>Check</button><span class='vocab-answer' data-correct='daughter' style='display:none;'></span></div><div style='display:flex; align-items:center; flex-wrap:wrap; gap:5px;'>6. Benny is Patrick's <select class='vocab-select'><option value=''>── select ──</option><option value='wife'>wife</option><option value='son'>son</option><option value='daughter'>daughter</option><option value='brother'>brother</option></select>.<button onclick='checkVocab(this)'>Check</button><span class='vocab-answer' data-correct='son' style='display:none;'></span></div></div>",
    "ja": "",
    "fr": "",
    "ko": ""
  },
